{"_id":"6HTEuUYVeR6zUXOK","name":"Bell Ringer","type":"feat","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/the-bellfounder.png","data":{"description":"<p>&ldquo;The&rdquo; bells of the Bellfounder seek to ring themselves. When you use a bell roll d20. If you succeed, then roll d4 to determine the bell&rsquo;s effect. A failure on an attempt to use the bell still succeeds, but to the detriment of the ringer. A fumble invokes an Arcane Catastrophe. A crit means the ringer has mastered the rolled power of the bell and may now use it intentionally. Any creature may sacrifice their turn to cover their ears and not hear a bell.</p>\n<p>When you get your first bell, roll d6 for &ldquo;The&rdquo; Bell Foundry. Every time a Bellfounder \"Gets Better\", they found a new bell rolling d8 in &ldquo;The&rdquo; Bell Foundry.</p>","rollFormula":"1d20","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":"Use Bell"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"8TrFu59c1zX6K3pu":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EZfdr9HaFv5Y2CeV"}}}
